Frontier Airlines plans to charge up to $100 to passengers who want to store their hand luggage on their flight.
Frontier Airlines intends to charge up to $100 for a piece of hand luggage and $2 for coffee or soda, even though the announcement on Wednesday said passengers could keep the whole can.
The new fee applies to hand luggage in the luggage compartment above the seat, small bags under the seat are still free.
Frontier said it charges $25 if the fee is paid in advance, and $100 for travelers who pay at the gate.
Frontier spokeswoman Kate O'Malley said the $100 fee is aimed at encouraging travelers to take care of the payment in advance.
